    <div class="faq-container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>What is the Social Service Unit (SSU)?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The Social Service Unit (SSU) is a student-led organization at Sherubtse College dedicated to community service and social welfare. We organize various activities including cleaning campaigns, volunteer work, and awareness programs to make a positive impact in our community and the Kanglung region.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>How can I become a member of SSU?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>To become a member:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Fill out the registration form on our website</li>
              <li>Submit valid Sherubtse student credentials</li>
              <li>Wait for approval from the SSU admin team</li>
              <li>Attend the orientation session at the college</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>What activities does SSU organize?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>SSU at Sherubtse College organizes various activities including:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Community cleaning campaigns in Kanglung</li>
              <li>Educational support for local schools</li>
              <li>Health awareness workshops</li>
              <li>Environmental conservation initiatives</li>
              <li>Cultural preservation activities</li>
              <li>Social outreach programs in Trashigang</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>How many hours of service are required?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Members are expected to complete a minimum of 20 hours of community service per semester. These hours can be accumulated through participation in various SSU activities and initiatives.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>Can I propose new service projects?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes! We encourage members to propose new service projects. You can:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Submit your proposal through the website</li>
              <li>Present your idea during monthly meetings</li>
              <li>Work with a mentor to develop your project</li>
              <li>Lead the implementation with team support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <h3>What are the benefits of joining SSU?</h3>
            <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
          </div>
